response: "{ \"title\": \"Easy: Divisor Sum\", \"description\": \"Given a positive integer `n`, calculate the sum of all proper divisors (excluding `n` itself) of `n`. Write a function `divisor_sum` that calculates this sum.\\n\\n#### Function Signature\\n```python\\ndef divisor_sum(n: int) -> int:\\n```\\n\\n#### Input\\n- `n` (int): A positive integer.\\n\\n#### Output\\n- Returns the sum of all proper divisors of `n`.\\n\", \"code\": \"def divisor_sum(n: int) -> int:\\n    sum = 0\\n    for i in range(1, n):\\n        if n % i == 0:\\n            sum += i\\n    return sum\\n\", \"tests\": [\"assert divisor_sum(28) == 28\", \"assert divisor_sum(12) == 10\", \"assert divisor_sum(13) == 1\", \"assert divisor_sum(24) == 28\"] }"
